AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GENEPIO_0001446> "Example Guidance: Provide an expanded description of why the sample was sequenced using pick list. The description may include the importance of the sequences for a particular public health investigation/surveillance activity/research question. Suggested standardized descriptions include: Screened for S gene target failure (S dropout), Screened for mink variants, Screened for B.1.1.7 variant, Screened for B.1.135 variant, Screened for P.1 variant, Screened due to travel history, Screened due to close contact with infected individual, Assessing public health control measures, Determining early introductions and spread, Investigating airline-related exposures, Investigating temporary foreign worker, Investigating remote regions, Investigating health care workers, Investigating schools/universities, Investigating reinfection."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GENEPIO_0001446> "purpose of sequencing details field"@en)
